    Save local repository's metadata collection Id

    When the enterprise connector is requested to update metadata,
    it needs to identify which store to redirect the request to.
    It does this by comparing the home collection Id in the
    instance with the metadata collection id assigned to each repository in the cohort.
    In the logic today, the code that is supposed to set up the variable containing the
    local repository's metadata collection id is actually setting its own metadata collection
    id in the super class rather than the local variable.

    This means that the enterprise connector is not able to find the repository that corresponds
    to the local repository.

    This is covered by Jira https://jira.odpi.org/browse/EGERIA-28

    Signed-off-by: Mandy Chessell <mandy_chessell@uk.ibm.com>
